text: DeKalb County is a county in the northwest part of the U.S. state of Missouri. As of the 2020 census, the population was 11,029.< The county seat is Maysville. The county was founded on February 25, 1845. It is named after General Johann de Kalb, Baron de Kalb, of the American Revolutionary War. == References == Category:1845 establishments in Missouri Category:Missouri counties
title: DeKalb County, Missouri
